Class TicTacToeHashMap

  • public class TicTacToeHashMap
extends java.lang.Object
    TicTacToeHashMap is a class to store winning TicTacToe Strings in a HashMap with String keys and boolean values. The class fills a hash map with the Strings than analyzes the map for aspects like capacity, load factor, and distribution. This class will mainly be used to analyze the efficiency of a hash map with Java's hashCode method as compared to other ways to store TicTacToe strings using hashing. Additionally, this class uses reflection in order to analyze the hash map considering the array in which the values are stored is not easily accessible, and HashMap.Entry, which is the type of array is not a public Java class.
